9. RGB CHANNEL MANIPULATION
------------------------------------------------------------

img_arr = np.asarray(Image.open('image.png'))
  - Opens image as NumPy array using PIL
  - Shape: (height, width, 3) for RGB

Isolating a single channel:
  pic_red = img_arr.copy()
  pic_red[:,:,1] = 0    # zero out green channel
  pic_red[:,:,2] = 0    # zero out blue channel
  plt.imshow(pic_red)   # shows only red component

Channel index reference:
  [:,:,0] = Red channel
  [:,:,1] = Green channel
  [:,:,2] = Blue channel

